item.description:
@508_Client wrote:

[quote=“MTMooreMT, post:1, topic:235484”]hey i once i do run cmd ip config i get this

[code] Ethernet adapter Hamachi:

    Connection-specific DNS Suffix  . :
    IP Address. . . . . . . . . . . . : 5.29.198.247
    Subnet Mask . . . . . . . . . . . : 255.0.0.0
    Default Gateway . . . . . . . . . :

Ethernet adapter Wireless Network Connection:

    Connection-specific DNS Suffix  . :
    IP Address. . . . . . . . . . . . : 192.168.0.2
    Subnet Mask . . . . . . . . . . . : 255.255.255.0
    Default Gateway . . . . . . . . . : 192.168.0.1[/code]

and on www.ipchicken.com i get 79.73.97.161
non of these ips work for other people to log onto my server can any1 help[/quote]

    [code]Default Gateway . . . . . . . . . : 192.168.0.1[/code]- router address.
   [code]IP Address. . . . . . . . . . . . : 192.168.0.2[/code] - default ip, not to be used for servers.

The IP from ipchicken should work. Since it’s not your port forward went wrong somewhere, either that or the wrong port is set in server.java
